@startuml likeComment
!include ../../theme/theme-dark-seq.puml
title likeComment flow
actor User
participant Resolver
participant CommentsService as C
participant LikesService as L
participant ActivityService as A
database DB

User -> Resolver: likeComment()
Resolver -> C: likeComment() : bool

group commentsRepo.manager.transaction
  C -> DB: manager.findOne(User)
  DB --> C: user

  C -> DB: lockEntityByIdOrThrow(Comment) + load user relation
  DB --> C: comment

  C -> DB: manager.findOne(Post)
  DB --> C: post

  C -> L: like()
  L -> DB: repo.findOne()
  DB --> L: like | null

  note over L,C
  Overall flow:
  - if like is already active, return success immediately
  - otherwise activate or create the like
  -- then log comment-like activity
  end note

  alt existing like is active
    L --> C: changed = false
    C -> C: skip activity log (idempotent)
  else like state changed
    alt existing inactive like
      L -> DB: repo.save() [active=false -> true]
      DB --> L: like reactivated
    else no existing like
      L -> DB: repo.save()
      DB --> L: like saved
    end
    L --> C: changed = true

    C -> A: logActivity()
    A -> DB: repo.query()
    DB --> A: activity row
    A --> C: activity
  end
end

C --> Resolver: true
Resolver --> User: data.likeComment = true

== Error rule ==
note over C,DB
If any awaited step inside the transaction throws:
TypeORM issues ROLLBACK, then error bubbles to resolver,
and resolver returns a GraphQL error.
end note
@enduml
